# Trivy baseline -- gate-on-new. The build's image-scan gate (HIGH/CRITICAL, ignore-unfixed)
# fails on any fixed-available CVE that is NOT listed here. This file is intentionally EMPTY of
# CVE entries: the image currently has zero accepted HIGH/CRITICAL findings, so any new one will
# (correctly) fail the gate. Keep the file present so the workflow's `trivyignores:` reference
# resolves and the gate-on-new posture is preserved.
#
# 2026-07-15 (#474 / SMP-1297): baseline EMPTIED. The final 8 accepted CVEs were all genuinely
# present in the image and fixable; they are now remediated at the image level instead of
# suppressed:
#   - JS: stale transitive braces 2.3.2 (CVE-2024-4068) and form-data 3.0.4 (CVE-2026-12143)
#     pulled forward via package.json overrides (braces 3.0.3, form-data 4.0.6).
#   - Ruby stdlib: base ruby:3.3.6-slim shipped stale default/bundled gemspecs -- uri 0.13.1
#     (CVE-2025-61594), zlib 3.1.1 (CVE-2026-27820), erb 4.0.3 (CVE-2026-41316) and net-imap
#     0.4.9.1 (CVE-2026-42245 / 42246 / 42257). The runtime stage now installs the patched
#     pure-Ruby gems (uri 0.13.3, net-imap 0.6.4.1) and drops the stale default gemspecs; the
#     patched erb 6.0.4 / zlib 3.2.3 come from the app bundle. See the Dockerfile "Ruby stdlib
#     CVE hardening" step. This is the proper fix for the #319 default-gem image-scan incident.
# Validated by an amd64 Trivy image scan (HIGH/CRITICAL, ignore-unfixed) = 0 findings.
#
# History: 2026-07-13 trimmed 70 stale entries against a live scan; 2026-07-15 emptied.
